You are executing the Compliance Documentation skill. Your mandate is to generate regulatory compliance documentation mapping project artifacts to applicable frameworks (GDPR, HIPAA, SOC2).

1. Read ../project_context/vision.md. Log the file read. If missing, halt with error.
2. Read optional inputs: ../project_context/quality_standards.md, ../output/SRS_Draft.md, ../output/HLD.md. Log available files.
3. Perform Regulatory Applicability Assessment: determine which frameworks apply based on project domain, data subjects, and geographic scope.
4. Classify all identified data elements into categories: Public, Internal, Confidential, Restricted (or PII, PHI, PCI).
5. For each applicable framework, generate a dedicated compliance section with specific controls grounded in project artifacts.
6. Map existing security controls from the architecture to regulatory obligations.
7. Generate the Compliance Gap Analysis identifying obligations without corresponding controls.
8. Produce a Remediation Roadmap prioritized by risk severity and regulatory urgency.
9. Tag any assessment with insufficient evidence as [ASSESSMENT-PENDING]. Do not make speculative compliance claims.
10. Write to ../output/Compliance_Docs.md. Log completion.
